<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,464,429,487]" box="[151,410,463,487]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
(
<figureCitation box="[158,256,463,487]" captionStart="PLATE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[162,1420,212,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[151,1435,195,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="PLATE 1. A–I. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Freytagolidia ligula, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Neodocalidia connectiva sp. nov., holotype; (C) Baluba sharkeyi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Bolidiana elongata, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov., holotype; (I) Jalorpa constricta, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Plate 1G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[268,402,463,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,202,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-81@18.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–56. Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov. (48) pygofer, lateral view; (49) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (50) right style, lateral view; (51) right style, dorsal view; (52) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (53) aedeagus, ventral view; (54) connective, dorsal view; (55) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (56) connective and base of aedeagus, dorsal view." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 48–56</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,535,1460]" box="[151,693,535,560]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,536,560]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 6.50–8.50 mm., female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,535,1460]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,459,572,596]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Large, robust species. General color dark brown to black; forewings with large ochraceous spot on apex of clavus; crown ochraceous, 2 dark brown, broad longitudinal bands medially on disk; eyes black (
<figureCitation box="[226,329,644,668]" captionStart="PLATE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[162,1420,212,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[151,1435,195,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="PLATE 1. A–I. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Freytagolidia ligula, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Neodocalidia connectiva sp. nov., holotype; (C) Baluba sharkeyi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Bolidiana elongata, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov., holotype; (I) Jalorpa constricta, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Plate 1G</figureCitation>
); face ochraceous, broad black longitudinal band on lateral margins of clypeus, extending distally, joined at apex; clypellus with medial ochraceous spots apically and basally. Head distinctly narrower than pronotum, anterior margin obtusely rounded; crown very broad, about 1/3 wider than width of eyes, produced distally about 1/3 of entire median length, lateral margins convergent basally, foveate on each side of middle, disk finely striate longitudinally; pronotum large, about equal in length of crown, surface smoothly rugulose transversely, sparsely bullated, finely setaceous; mesonotum very large, about half again as long as pronotum; forewings long, very broad, 3 anteapical cells present, outer one closed; clypeus very long, narrow, lateral margins broadly convex; median longitudinal carina faint; clypellus short, less than 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow, lateral margins parallel in basal ¾, apex expanded laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,535,1460]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,967,992]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view subtriangulate, small lobe with setae on caudodorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,968,992]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,202,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-81@18.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–56. Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov. (48) pygofer, lateral view; (49) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (50) right style, lateral view; (51) right style, dorsal view; (52) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (53) aedeagus, ventral view; (54) connective, dorsal view; (55) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (56) connective and base of aedeagus, dorsal view." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate long, narrow, sinuate, setaceous in distal 2/5 (
<figureCitation box="[904,988,1004,1028]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,202,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-81@18.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–56. Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov. (48) pygofer, lateral view; (49) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (50) right style, lateral view; (51) right style, dorsal view; (52) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (53) aedeagus, ventral view; (54) connective, dorsal view; (55) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (56) connective and base of aedeagus, dorsal view." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
); style shorter than aedeagus, apophysis long, very narrow, slightly inflated apically (
<figureCitation box="[657,796,1040,1064]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,202,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-81@18.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–56. Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov. (48) pygofer, lateral view; (49) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (50) right style, lateral view; (51) right style, dorsal view; (52) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (53) aedeagus, ventral view; (54) connective, dorsal view; (55) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (56) connective and base of aedeagus, dorsal view." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 50, 51</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long with shaft bifurcate at middle, in lateral view, ventral bifurcation inflated medially with dorsal spines, 4 subapical spines, one very long projecting anteriorly, dorsal bifurcation glabrous, in dorsal view very broad medially, lyrate from base to apex (
<figureCitation box="[1226,1364,1112,1136]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,202,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-81@18.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–56. Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov. (48) pygofer, lateral view; (49) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (50) right style, lateral view; (51) right style, dorsal view; (52) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (53) aedeagus, ventral view; (54) connective, dorsal view; (55) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (56) connective and base of aedeagus, dorsal view." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 52, 53</figureCitation>
); connective lying dorsad of base of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[644,731,1148,1172]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,202,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-81@18.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–56. Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov. (48) pygofer, lateral view; (49) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (50) right style, lateral view; (51) right style, dorsal view; (52) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (53) aedeagus, ventral view; (54) connective, dorsal view; (55) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (56) connective and base of aedeagus, dorsal view." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
), nearly T-shaped, narrow membrane, rib absent, stem short, bulbous apically (
<figureCitation box="[350,434,1184,1208]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,202,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-81@18.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–56. Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov. (48) pygofer, lateral view; (49) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (50) right style, lateral view; (51) right style, dorsal view; (52) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (53) aedeagus, ventral view; (54) connective, dorsal view; (55) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (56) connective and base of aedeagus, dorsal view." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective long, apical half expanded, base broad (
<figureCitation box="[1104,1188,1184,1208]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,202,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-81@18.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–56. Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov. (48) pygofer, lateral view; (49) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (50) right style, lateral view; (51) right style, dorsal view; (52) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (53) aedeagus, ventral view; (54) connective, dorsal view; (55) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (56) connective and base of aedeagus, dorsal view." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
