<subSubSection box="[199,1320,1328,1352]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,535,1460]" box="[199,1320,1328,1352]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,1328,1352]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is descriptive for the configuration of the ventral bifurcation of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,535,1460]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1364,1388]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is very near to 
<taxonomicName box="[628,766,1364,1388]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Harasupia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulata">
<emphasis box="[628,766,1364,1388]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. pustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[781,944,1364,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 124–132" captionStartId="37.[151,264,1941,1964]" captionTargetBox="[195,1369,202,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-73@37.[183,1382,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 124–132. Stalolidia flangella, sp.nov. (124) pygofer, lateral view; (125) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (126) right style, lateral view; (127) right style, dorsal view; (128) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (129) aedeagus, ventral view; (130) connective, dorsal view; (131) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (132) apex of style, detail, ventral view." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 131, 132</figureCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nielson, M. W." box="[955,1113,1364,1388]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 329" refId="ref33690" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1979 e) A revision of the subfamily Coelidiinae (Homptera: Cicadellidae). III. Tribe Teruliini. Pacific Insects - Monograph, 35 1 - 329." type="journal article" year="1979">Nielson, 1979</bibRefCitation>
) and can be distinguished by the inflated ventral arm of the bifurcated aedeagus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[941,1029,1400,1424]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,202,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-81@18.[151,1436,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–56. Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov. (48) pygofer, lateral view; (49) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (50) right style, lateral view; (51) right style, dorsal view; (52) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (53) aedeagus, ventral view; (54) connective, dorsal view; (55) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (56) connective and base of aedeagus, dorsal view." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
), by the sinuate plate (49) and the slightly inflated apex of the style in dorsal view (51).
</paragraph>
